{"id":14881791,"mediaExerciseId":"d3156922-f7f6-4969-9abf-b0510518dfe5","exerciseName":"4","chapterName":"21","chapterTitle":"International Corporate Finance","groupId":612473,"groupTitle":"Minicase Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":739,"solutions":[{"id":5996370,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we are asked how will the company hedge the exchange rate risk. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":61,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/446f9b43e3c845ec490f7fdf7ecb4d49/425ad9b8b35f753fd79c96050904dd79/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":32,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/446f9b43e3c845ec490f7fdf7ecb4d49/425ad9b8b35f753fd79c96050904dd79/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"**Exchange rate** risk is the natural consequence in the international market where the value of the *currencies either increase or decrease*. **Hedging** is a technique to *limit the risk* of the company.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/446f9b43e3c845ec490f7fdf7ecb4d49/2a5655fd73036f1ee3d1d442b3db3238/lateximg_large.png","width":1003},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/446f9b43e3c845ec490f7fdf7ecb4d49/2a5655fd73036f1ee3d1d442b3db3238/lateximg.png","width":501}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"To hedge the exchange rate risk, the company can enter a **forward trade**. A **forward trade** is an agreement to *exchange currency in the future*. The *exchange rate in the agreement* of a forward trade is called a **forward exchange rate**.\n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":143,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/446f9b43e3c845ec490f7fdf7ecb4d49/1625e66f6064b2c941ade43559ef8d4f/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/446f9b43e3c845ec490f7fdf7ecb4d49/1625e66f6064b2c941ade43559ef8d4f/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"When entering a forward trade, it is assumed that the value of the currency weakens since the company hedge in order not to incur a loss. Therefore, the value of the exchange rate in the forward trade is greater than the value of the exchange rate in the future.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":141,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/446f9b43e3c845ec490f7fdf7ecb4d49/3d58fa284f12bcb0968b8732d3c5e4dc/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/446f9b43e3c845ec490f7fdf7ecb4d49/3d58fa284f12bcb0968b8732d3c5e4dc/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"As a conclusion, the company can hedge the exchange rate risk by **entering into a forward trade**. However, this implies that the **dollar weakens** in the future.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":100,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/446f9b43e3c845ec490f7fdf7ecb4d49/88c08be60398deafd4e69186a03b128d/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":51,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/08/446f9b43e3c845ec490f7fdf7ecb4d49/88c08be60398deafd4e69186a03b128d/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"f01dd6a1-9b74-46e3-a7d4-9855fd8bef3f","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":5}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881792,"exerciseName":"5","page":739,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"f998b729-be6b-4959-8426-6be74c071e39","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-21-minicase-questions-5-f998b729-be6b-4959-8426-6be74c071e39"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881790,"exerciseName":"3","page":739,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"41b9d8c1-b3e5-4873-8f45-2ab6cadaeece","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-21-minicase-questions-3-41b9d8c1-b3e5-4873-8f45-2ab6cadaeece"},{"id":14881789,"exerciseName":"2","page":739,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"9006616d-e679-4439-ab36-ad929188cc2d","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-21-minicase-questions-2-9006616d-e679-4439-ab36-ad929188cc2d"}],"_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-21-minicase-questions-4-d3156922-f7f6-4969-9abf-b0510518dfe5"}